Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a yellow ball, Bob has a blue ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Claire and Alice swap balls. Then, Alice and Bob swap balls. Finally, Claire and Bob swap balls. At the end of the game, Bob has the
Options:
(A) yellow ball
(B) blue ball
(C) pink ball
A: (A)

Q: In a game of musical chairs, five people - Alice, Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve - are sitting around a table with five empty chairs. Alice starts in the first chair, Bob in the second, Claire in the third, Dave in the fourth, and Eve in the fifth.
As the game begins, the people start moving around the table, sitting in the empty chairs. First, Bob and Claire trade places. Then, Dave and Eve trade places. Finally, Bob and Claire trade places again. In the end, the person sitting in the third chair is
Options:
(A) Alice
(B) Bob
(C) Claire
(D) Dave
(E) Eve
A: (B)||
